---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Extended Advanced Diploma — Year 1 of the PhD | Brenkley Doctoral College" description="The Extended Advanced Diploma is Year 1 of the Brenkley Doctoral College PhD, equivalent to Year 1 of a PhD — SCQF Level 11, 180 credits, delivered fully online with an embedded professional internship. Articulates directly into PhD Year 2 at a partner university. £10,000 for Year 1.">

  <section class="bg-surface border-b border-border py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-4">Programme &mdash; Year 1 of the PhD &mdash; Delivered Online</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Extended Advanced Diploma</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-accent font-medium mb-4">SCQF Level 11 &mdash; 180 Credits &mdash; Includes Applied Internship &mdash; £10,000 for Year 1</p>
      <p class="text-lg text-muted max-w-2xl">The Extended Advanced Diploma is Year 1 of the Brenkley Doctoral College PhD, equivalent to Year 1 of a PhD — a substantive, credit-rated qualification for professionals who want to conduct supervised original research and put theory into practice through a structured internship. Delivered entirely online, credit-rated at SCQF Level 11 (180 credits), it is a recognised and respected standalone qualification, and also the foundation year for progression directly into PhD Year 2 at one of our partner universities — with a UK Student (CAS) visa route available for Year 2 onward for international researchers.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-4 gap-6 mb-12">
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">18–24 Months</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted">Part-time, delivered fully online</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">SCQF Level 11</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted">180 credits within the Scottish Credit and Qualifications Framework</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">Internship Included</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted">Applied placement putting research theory into professional practice</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">£10,000</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted">Single Year 1 fee, regardless of whether completed in 18 or 24 months</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
        <div>
          <p class="section-label mb-3">About the Extended Advanced Diploma</p>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Research and Practice at the Highest Pre-Doctoral Level</h2>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">The Extended Advanced Diploma is a research degree, not a taught postgraduate qualification. It requires you to design and conduct an original research project, submit a substantial thesis (typically 40,000–60,000 words), pass an oral examination, and complete a supervised internship applying your research theory to a live professional context. It is a meaningful intellectual achievement and a recognised academic qualification.</p>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">Credit-rated at SCQF Level 11 (180 credits) — the level and credit weight of the first year of a Scottish doctoral degree — it enables recognition and potential credit transfer within the UK higher education system.</p>
          <p class="text-muted">Successful completion is recognised as Year 1 of the Brenkley Doctoral College PhD, with the option to progress directly into PhD Year 2 at one of our partner universities — continuing through to PhD graduation, normally at the end of Year 3 for full-time students — or to a DBA or EdD.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="section-label mb-3">Who Should Apply</p>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Is the Extended Advanced Diploma Right for You?</h2>
          <div class="space-y-3">
            <div class="card">
              <p class="text-muted text-sm">You want to conduct rigorous original research but are not ready to commit to three or more years of doctoral study.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
              <p class="text-muted text-sm">You want a recognised research qualification, backed by real-world applied experience, to advance your professional or academic career without a full doctorate.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
              <p class="text-muted text-sm">You are testing whether doctoral-level research is for you, with the option to progress to a full doctorate at a partner university if you wish.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
              <p class="text-muted text-sm">You have a specific, bounded research question that can be addressed in 18–24 months of part-time study, and want to put your findings into practice through an internship.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Structure -->
  <section class="bg-surface border-y border-border py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">Programme Structure</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">18–24 Months to the Extended Advanced Diploma</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-bold mb-3 text-accent">Stage 1 (Months 1–9)</h3>
          <ul class="text-muted text-sm space-y-2">
            <li>Introduction to Research Methods module</li>
            <li>Literature review development</li>
            <li>Research design and ethics approval</li>
            <li>Research proposal submission and approval</li>
            <li>Supervision meetings (minimum 6 in first nine months)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-bold mb-3 text-accent">Stage 2 (Months 10–18/24)</h3>
          <ul class="text-muted text-sm space-y-2">
            <li>Data collection and analysis</li>
            <li>Thesis writing with supervisor feedback</li>
            <li>Progress review at month 12</li>
            <li>Thesis submission (40,000–60,000 words)</li>
            <li>Oral examination (viva voce)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-bold mb-3 text-accent">Applied Internship</h3>
          <ul class="text-muted text-sm space-y-2">
            <li>Structured placement in a professional or organisational setting</li>
            <li>Direct application of your research theory and findings to practice</li>
            <li>Supervised and assessed alongside your thesis work</li>
            <li>Internship outcomes report contributes to final credit award</li>
            <li>Award of the Extended Advanced Diploma (SCQF 11, 180 credits)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Internship Routes -->
  <section id="internship" class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">The Internship</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Two Ways Into Your Internship</h2>
      <p class="text-muted mb-8 max-w-3xl">The internship is what turns Year 1 from a research exercise into applied practice. Most of our learners are already in professional roles, so we built the internship around two routes into a placement — whichever fits your circumstances.</p>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
        <div class="card">
          <p class="section-label mb-2">Route 1 — Learner-Sourced</p>
          <h3 class="font-bold mb-3">Bring Your Own Organisation</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">If you are already employed, you can propose your own workplace as your internship host. Your research is applied directly to a live challenge or project within your organisation, with your employer's agreement and our supervision framework in place.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <p class="section-label mb-2">Route 2 — Organisation-Sourced</p>
          <h3 class="font-bold mb-3">Matched Through Our Employer Network</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">Organisations apply directly to Brenkley Doctoral College in one of two ways: to register an existing employee onto Year 1 of the PhD with an internship built around their role, or to bring forward a specific project that needs a researcher, which we match with a suitable learner. See <a href="/connect/" class="text-accent underline">Partnership Enquiries</a> to register interest.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card max-w-3xl">
        <p class="text-sm text-muted"><strong class="text-foreground">Either way, the same assurance applies:</strong> every placement runs under a structured learning contract, dual supervision (academic and workplace), agreed deliverables, and the legal and ethical safeguards (NDA, IP, data protection) set out in our internship agreements.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Progression -->
  <section class="bg-surface border-y border-border py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">Progression</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Your Choice of Partner University for PhD Year 2 Onward</h2>
      <p class="text-muted mb-8 max-w-3xl">The Extended Advanced Diploma stands on its own as a completed qualification, equivalent to Year 1 of a PhD. If you wish to continue to a full PhD, you choose which partner university you progress to — articulating directly into PhD Year 2 and continuing through to PhD graduation, normally at the end of Year 3 for full-time students — rather than being assigned one.</p>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Choice of Institution</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">Brenkley Doctoral College maintains progression arrangements with a network of partner universities. You select the institution that best fits your research area, career goals, and circumstances.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Subject to Admission</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">Progression is via each university's own articulation process into PhD Year 2. Your Extended Advanced Diploma and Year 1 credits support your application, but acceptance is confirmed by the partner university's admissions process, not guaranteed automatically.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">UK Student (CAS) Visa Route</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">Year 1 with Brenkley Doctoral College is delivered entirely online, so it can be completed from anywhere in the world. International researchers who progress to PhD Year 2 can then move to the UK under a Student (CAS) visa sponsored by their chosen partner university.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">No Obligation to Progress</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">There is no requirement to continue. Many learners complete the Extended Advanced Diploma as a standalone qualification and career milestone in its own right.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Requirements -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">Entry Requirements</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">What We Look For</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Academic</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">Bachelor's degree at 2:1 or above, or equivalent. A postgraduate qualification is not required, though applicants with a Master's degree are welcome. Strong professional portfolios are considered alongside academic qualifications.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Professional</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">Relevant professional experience is valued but not strictly required at the level demanded by our doctoral programmes. The Extended Advanced Diploma is appropriate for earlier-career professionals as well as senior practitioners, and your internship placement can draw on your existing sector or a new one.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Research Statement</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">A short research statement of 500–800 words outlining your proposed research area, its significance, and your initial thoughts on methodology. This is discussed and developed at interview.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-surface border-t border-border py-16 px-6 text-center">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Start with Year 1 of the PhD — Online</h2>
      <p class="text-muted mb-8">The Extended Advanced Diploma is a meaningful first step into research and practice, delivered entirely online. Apply today and begin the process of becoming a research-active professional — with a real qualification and an internship to show for it, whether or not you continue to PhD Year 2 at a partner university.</p>
      <div class="flex gap-4 justify-center flex-wrap">
        <a href="/apply" class="btn-primary">Apply now</a>
        <a href="/connect" class="btn-outline">Speak to us</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
